      <h1>Simplex Pattern Library</h1>
      <p><b>Simplex</b> is a simple, scalable framework that can be used as a
      base for complex websites and web applications. The word "simplex" comes
      from the Latin for "simple".</p>
      <p><b>Simplex</b> uses <a href="http://bem.info/">BEM</a> and
      <a href="http://oocss.org/">OOCSS</a> principles, and aims is to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>define base HTML markup</li>
        <li>define element styles</li>
        <li>define flexible form and table markup and styling</li>
        <li>define a series of re-usable modules, modifiers and sub-modules</li>
        <li>define a series of helper classes</li>
        <li>define a simple grid system that can be adjusted as needed</li>
      </ul>

<!-- @import "helpers/color-core" -->

      <h3><a href="01-elements.html">Elements</a></h3>
      <p>A wide range of HTML elements already styled for use.</p>

      <h3><a href="02-helpers.html">Helpers</a></h3>
      <p>Helper classes can be used to tweak aspects of the layout without having to write specific CSS components.</p>

      <h3><a href="03-modules.html">Modules</a></h3>
      <p>Modules are re-usable components that have been abstracted down to a single purpose. They are completely "de-coupled" from the HTML - which means that they can be placed anywhere within web pages - regardless of any parent elements or classes.</p>

      <h3><a href="04-grid.html">Grid</a></h3>
      <p>This is a simple 12 column grad based on the <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/">Bootstrap Grid</a> - with some extra flexibility.</p>

